Sentencas: Composites of Nb-doped strontium titanate mixed with yttria-stabilized zirconia or cerium oxide in 50:50, 70:30 and 85:15 weight ratios were evaluated as possible anode/electrolyte interface materials for solid oxide fuel cells in terms of chemical compatibility, electrical conductivity and mechanical properties.
Titulo: The comparison of SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-CeO2 and SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-YSZ composites for use in SOFC anodes

Sentencas: It has been shown that composite samples prepared by typical powder-mixing methods remain single-phase up to 1400A degrees
Titulo: The comparison of SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-CeO2 and SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-YSZ composites for use in SOFC anodes
The comparison of SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-CeO2 and SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-YSZ composites for use in SOFC anodes

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of these composites, regardless of their composition and fabrication conditions, is lower than the conductivity of pure SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-delta, but in most cases sufficient for solid oxide fuel cells anode application.
Titulo: The comparison of SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-CeO2 and SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-YSZ composites for use in SOFC anodes

Sentencas: The best properties are found for samples reduced at 1400A degrees C for 10 h in H-2 atmosphere.
Titulo: The comparison of SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-CeO2 and SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-YSZ composites for use in SOFC anodes

Sentencas: The observations made by scanning electron microscope suggest that the grains of both phases are well-distributed throughout the whole volume of the investigated samples, and that the composites with CeO2 better adhere to the electrolyte surface.
Titulo: The comparison of SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-CeO2 and SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-YSZ composites for use in SOFC anodes

Sentencas: The electrical results confirm that composites with at most 30 wt % of YSZ/CeO2 phase fulfill the anode requirements.
Titulo: The comparison of SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-CeO2 and SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-YSZ composites for use in SOFC anodes

Sentencas: However, the fuel cell performance tests indicate that the application of composite with CeO2 results in the lower power density than the application of the composite with YSZ.
Titulo: The comparison of SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-CeO2 and SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ-YSZ composites for use in SOFC anodes
